        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 8:51AM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 849 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southeast of Cornudas, moving east at 40 mph. This storm is
moving toward highway 62 180 between Cornudas and Salt Flat.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dell City and Salt Flat.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
